Summary: Folder Tidy style organizer CLI for source/destination folders
Requires-Python: >=3.9
Description-Content-Type: text/markdown

# downloads-organize

Folder Tidy style organizer CLI for macOS-like workflows.

## What It Supports

- `tidy` with default dry-run and `--apply` for real moves
- Source/Destination split (`--source`, `--destination`)
- 22 built-in rules (with `folders` and `aliases` default off)
- Configurable custom rules with predicate-like conditions
- Ignore controls (`extensions`, `paths`, aliases/folders/tagged)
- Collision-safe destination naming (`name (1).ext`)
- Undo history (`undo`, `undo-list`, `undo-delete`)

## Quick Start

```bash
python3 -m downloads_organize tidy --source ~/Downloads --destination ~/TidyBox
python3 -m downloads_organize tidy --source ~/Downloads --destination ~/TidyBox --apply
python3 -m downloads_organize undo-list
python3 -m downloads_organize undo --apply
```

## Commands

- `tidy`: organize files using enabled rules
- `rules-list`: print effective rule list
- `undo-list`: list transaction history
- `undo`: restore latest pending transaction (or `--id <tx_id>`)
- `undo-delete`: delete history entries (`--id` or `--older-than-days`)

## Config (TOML)

```toml
[rules]
disable = ["screenshots"]
order = ["custom_recent_shots", "pdf_documents", "word_documents"]

[extension_rules]
code = [".log"]

[ignore]
extensions = [".crdownload", ".part"]
paths = ["Thumbs.db", "source/.DS_Store"]
aliases = true
folders = false
tagged = false

[options]
include_subfolders = true
skip_bundles = true
remove_empty_folders = true
create_dated_top_folder = false

[custom_rules.recent_shots]
description = "Screenshots from the last 2 weeks"
subfolder = "Recent Screenshots"
mode = "all"
enabled = true
kind = "image_png"
name_contains = "screenshot"
created_within_days = 14
```

Condition keys for custom rules:

- `kind`
- `name_contains`
- `created_within_days`
- `size_gte`
- `size_lte`
- `extensions`
